    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n3785" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἕρκος</span></b> , <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">εος</span> (<span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ϝέργω</span>):
            <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">hedge, wall</span>, then the <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">enclosure</span>
          itself, i. e. the court, <i><span class="en">Il. 24.306</span></i>,
          pl., <i><span class="en">Od. 8.57</span></i>, etc.; <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">bulwark,
            defence</span> against, <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἀκόντων, βελέων, Δ
            137</span>, <i><span class="en">Il. 5.316</span></i>; said of
          persons, <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἕρκος πολέμοιο, ἕρκος Ἀχαιῶν, Α
            284</span>, <i><span class="en">Il. 3.229</span></i> (cf.
            <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">πύργος</span>); <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἕρκος
            ὀδόντων</span> (the ‘fence of the teeth’), used in connections
          where we should always say ‘lips.’</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
